From fb168dcbc2981a012cc3bed74e944425ac23157d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 12:55:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add "Validate" view: SupplyScope product-idea research merged
 into RSI

Ports SupplyScope's "submit a product idea -> multi-agent research &
benchmark" capability into the dashboard as a new "Validate" view, restyled
into the NxB plain-CSS design system (no Tailwind). The existing snapshot/
trends pipeline and views are otherwise untouched.

- web/components/views/ideas.tsx: submission form, animated pipeline,
  results (benchmark, suppliers, makers, strategy analysis, sources) and a
  "Recently validated" read-back list (View reopens past results).
- web/components/views/insights.tsx: completed ideas also surface as scored
  procurement insights (client-side fetch of /api/ideas; live Supabase or the
  in-memory store), tagged "Validate" and counted in a "From Validate" tile.
- web/app/api/ideas[/[id]/research]: server routes (nodejs, force-dynamic);
  keys ANTHROPIC_API_KEY||RSI_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, FIRECRAWL_API_KEY,
  APIFY_API_TOKEN; deterministic demo data when no keys are set.
- web/lib/ideas/*: ported agent logic (Claude via raw fetch, Firecrawl,
  Apify), server-only service-role writes, in-memory fallback (no disk).
- integration.ts fans research onto product_categories/suppliers/
  competitors + a triggers row; never writes snapshots or insights.
- pipelines/src/rsi/models.py: ProductIdea model (incl. category, audience,
  features, submitted_by); supabase/migrations/0006_product_ideas.sql.
- web/.env.example: ANTHROPIC/FIRECRAWL/APIFY + SUPABASE service-role keys.

Build, typecheck, and lint pass.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
